description:
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy has arisen for Clinic Clerk within the Surgical elective admissions unit (SEAL) The successful candidate will be based at Arrowe Park.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a self motivated and enthusiastic person to take on a challenging and sometimes pressurised role. The successful candidate will have excellent communication and organisational skills with the ability to work on their own initiative and as part of a multi-disciplinary team. Previous hospital experience is desirable. You should have a polite, friendly manner, and be able to deal with sensitive and confidential information professionally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate should be competent with both telephone and computer skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shift pattern: 12 pm to 7pm or 11 am to 6 pm (variable) **Please note A&amp;C work on a rota and the successful candidate will be required to work some shifts until 8pm* During holiday period, there maybe a requirement for a 7 am -5pm shift cover.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For a initial chat or walkaround please contact Andrew.bradley-gibbons@nhs.net or 678-5111 ex 7149&lt;/p&gt;
